    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 300°F (150°C) for smoking.",
    "Season the roast beef with cumin, chili powder, and garlic.",
    "Place the beef on a wooden board and roast for 2 hours, smoke flavor will be achieved by adding wood chips to the oven.",
    "While the beef is roasting, chop the saskatoon berries and toss with lime juice to prevent browning.",
    "Once the beef is cooked, slice it thinly and set aside.",
    "Roast the poblano peppers over an open flame or in the oven until charred, peel and chop.",
    "Warm the tortillas by wrapping them in a damp paper towel and microwaving for 20 seconds.",
    "Assemble the tacos by placing a few slices of beef onto a tortilla, topping with saskatoon berry salsa, and finishing with a sprinkle of cumin and chili powder."
  ],
